      <h1 class='title'>NHS Purchasing and Supply Agency</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1761WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1761ws' title='Col. 1761WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1761WS' name='column_1761ws' href='#column_1761ws' rel='bookmark'>1761WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_610'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-mark-oaten' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_610' title='Link to this speech by Mr Mark Oaten' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-mark-oaten" title="Mr Mark Oaten">Mr. Oaten</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Health what long-term plans he has for the NHS Purchasing and Supply Agency. [187118]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_611'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-rosie-winterton' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_611' title='Link to this speech by Ms Rosie Winterton' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-rosie-winterton" title="Ms Rosie Winterton">Ms Rosie Winterton</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">Proposals for the reconfiguration of the National Health Service Purchasing and Supply Agency (NHS PASA) are outlined in a report, "Reconfiguring the Department of Health's Arm's Length Bodies", published on 22 July 2004. It is proposed that NHS PASA will be reshaped as part of a major programme to support the NHS in handling purchasing and supply more effectively. The Department's commercial directorate has developed plans to streamline the supply chain in the NHS. As these plans are implemented, a transformed NHS PASA will play a crucial role in applying procurement best practice to maximise savings. NHS PASA should be able to take on procurement and contracting functions from other arm's length bodies (ALBs), helping to reduce the cost of the ALB sector.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
